{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place simmering basket onto mixing bowl lid and weigh rice into it. Rinse rice until water runs clear. Set aside.","Place garlic into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>2 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>.","Add onion and chop <nobr>1 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add stock paste and water. Insert simmering basket with rice and cook <nobr>15 min\/100°C\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and set aside.","Add yoghurt then mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>, adding egg through hole in mixing bowl lid, until combined.","Cook <nobr>4 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<\/nobr>, until slightly thickened.","Add salt, pepper and cooked rice and cook <nobr>3 min\/100°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Transfer into a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl and cover to keep warm.","Place a frying pan (19 cm) over medium-high heat and add butter. Once butter is foaming, add chickpeas, chilli flakes and kale and fry until chickpeas are just starting to crisp (3-5 minutes).","Divide soup between 20 small cups and sprinkle with chickpea mixture to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["80 g medium grain rice","1 garlic clove","120 g brown onion, cut into halves","1 tbsp Vegetable stock paste (see Tips)","800 g water","300 g Greek yoghurt","1 egg","salt, to taste","freshly ground black pepper, to taste","1 ½ tbsp unsalted butter","400 g canned chickpeas, rinsed and drained (approx. 200 g after draining)","½ - 1 tbsp dried chilli flakes","3 stalks kale, stalks removed and leaves finely chopped"]}],"id":"r119892","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-adqVQaYfgjM\/XZMuZfNxyaI\/AAAAAAAAaEw\/Aozad7Xjof8FvW1BexP3y0TifBJkb_wGwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_HAEtGX1IghxG1Eu9.png","title":"Yoghurt soup cups","publishedAt":"2017-01-22T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2.2 g","fat":"2.3 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"7.1 g","calories":"252 kJ \/ 60 kcal"},"usefulItems":"thermal serving bowl or other large bowl, frying pan (19 cm), 20 small cups or serving glasses, stove top","hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook <\/em>or <em>Everyday Cookbook <\/em>for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","You can replace kale with silverbeet.","This yoghurt soup can also be a sauce for grilled meats or vegetables.","You can also serve this as an entrée at a dinner party."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","1h 10m","20 portions"]}